{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":804,"text":"What is it that French people\ndo better than all the others?"},{"time":6454,"text":"If you would take polls,"},{"time":8404,"text":"the top three answers might be:"},{"time":10235,"text":"love, wine and whining."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14298,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":15623,"text":"Maybe."},{"time":17530,"text":"But let me suggest a fourth one:"},{"time":19892,"text":"mathematics."},{"time":21760,"text":"Did you know that Paris\nhas more mathematicians"},{"time":24637,"text":"than any other city in the world?"},{"time":26801,"text":"And more streets\nwith mathematicians' names, too."},{"time":30215,"text":"And if you look at the statistics\nof the Fields Medal,"},{"time":33688,"text":"often called the Nobel Prize\nfor mathematics,"},{"time":36205,"text":"and always awarded to mathematicians\nbelow the age of 40,"},{"time":40161,"text":"you will find that France has more\nFields medalists per inhabitant"},{"time":44072,"text":"than any other country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46286,"text":"What is it that we find so sexy in math?"},{"time":50153,"text":"After all, it seems to be\ndull and abstract,"},{"time":53381,"text":"just numbers and computations\nand rules to apply."},{"time":58518,"text":"Mathematics may be abstract,"},{"time":60654,"text":"but it's not dull"},{"time":61829,"text":"and it's not about computing."},{"time":64178,"text":"It is about reasoning"},{"time":65949,"text":"and proving our core activity."},{"time":68513,"text":"It is about imagination,"},{"time":70059,"text":"the talent which we most praise."},{"time":72102,"text":"It is about finding the truth."},{"time":75613,"text":"There's nothing like the feeling\nwhich invades you"},{"time":78374,"text":"when after months of hard thinking,"},{"time":80569,"text":"you finally understand the right\nreasoning to solve your problem."},{"time":85042,"text":"The great mathematician\nAndr√© Weil likened this --"},{"time":88642,"text":"no kidding --"},{"time":89817,"text":"to sexual pleasure."},{"time":92197,"text":"But noted that this feeling\ncan last for hours, or even days."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98804,"text":"The reward may be big."},{"time":101325,"text":"Hidden mathematical truths\npermeate our whole physical world."},{"time":105680,"text":"They are inaccessible to our senses"},{"time":108374,"text":"but can be seen\nthrough mathematical lenses."},{"time":112092,"text":"Close your eyes for moment"},{"time":113708,"text":"and think of what is occurring\nright now around you."},{"time":118337,"text":"Invisible particles from the air\naround are bumping on you"},{"time":121854,"text":"by the billions and billions\nat each second,"},{"time":124611,"text":"all in complete chaos."},{"time":127049,"text":"And still,"},{"time":128224,"text":"their statistics can be accurately\npredicted by mathematical physics."},{"time":133715,"text":"And open your eyes now"},{"time":136531,"text":"to the statistics of the velocities\nof these particles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140510,"text":"The famous bell-shaped Gauss Curve,"},{"time":143774,"text":"or the Law of Errors --"},{"time":145979,"text":"of deviations with respect\nto the mean behavior."},{"time":149550,"text":"This curve tells about the statistics\nof velocities of particles"},{"time":153876,"text":"in the same way as a demographic curve"},{"time":156439,"text":"would tell about the statistics\nof ages of individuals."},{"time":160884,"text":"It's one of the most\nimportant curves ever."},{"time":164137,"text":"It keeps on occurring again and again,"},{"time":167347,"text":"from many theories and many experiments,"},{"time":169774,"text":"as a great example of the universality"},{"time":173079,"text":"which is so dear to us mathematicians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177694,"text":"Of this curve,"},{"time":178945,"text":"the famous scientist Francis Galton said,"},{"time":182018,"text":"\"It would have been deified by the Greeks\nif they had known it."},{"time":187064,"text":"It is the supreme law of unreason.\""},{"time":191818,"text":"And there's no better way to materialize\nthat supreme goddess than Galton's Board."},{"time":199774,"text":"Inside this board are narrow tunnels"},{"time":202995,"text":"through which tiny balls\nwill fall down randomly,"},{"time":208295,"text":"going right or left, or left, etc."},{"time":214139,"text":"All in complete randomness and chaos."},{"time":218085,"text":"Let's see what happens when we look\nat all these random trajectories together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224189,"text":"(Board shaking)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":229648,"text":"This is a bit of a sport,"},{"time":232516,"text":"because we need to resolve\nsome traffic jams in there."},{"time":239715,"text":"Aha."},{"time":241313,"text":"We think that randomness\nis going to play me a trick on stage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247609,"text":"There it is."},{"time":250382,"text":"Our supreme goddess of unreason."},{"time":252989,"text":"the Gauss Curve,"},{"time":254532,"text":"trapped here inside this transparent box\nas Dream in \"The Sandman\" comics."},{"time":262623,"text":"For you I have shown it,"},{"time":265345,"text":"but to my students I explain why\nit could not be any other curve."},{"time":271128,"text":"And this is touching\nthe mystery of that goddess,"},{"time":274022,"text":"replacing a beautiful coincidence\nby a beautiful explanation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279027,"text":"All of science is like this."},{"time":282213,"text":"And beautiful mathematical explanations\nare not only for our pleasure."},{"time":287585,"text":"They also change our vision of the world."},{"time":291040,"text":"For instance,"},{"time":292301,"text":"Einstein,"},{"time":293476,"text":"Perrin,"},{"time":294651,"text":"Smoluchowski,"},{"time":295826,"text":"they used the mathematical analysis\nof random trajectories"},{"time":299409,"text":"and the Gauss Curve"},{"time":301470,"text":"to explain and prove that our\nworld is made of atoms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307524,"text":"It was not the first time"},{"time":309350,"text":"that mathematics was revolutionizing\nour view of the world."},{"time":313555,"text":"More than 2,000 years ago,"},{"time":315791,"text":"at the time of the ancient Greeks,"},{"time":319502,"text":"it already occurred."},{"time":321827,"text":"In those days,"},{"time":323137,"text":"only a small fraction of the world\nhad been explored,"},{"time":326444,"text":"and the Earth might have seemed infinite."},{"time":330034,"text":"But clever Eratosthenes,"},{"time":331825,"text":"using mathematics,"},{"time":333266,"text":"was able to measure the Earth\nwith an amazing accuracy of two percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339969,"text":"Here's another example."},{"time":342238,"text":"In 1673, Jean Richer noticed"},{"time":346067,"text":"that a pendulum swings slightly\nslower in Cayenne than in Paris."},{"time":354350,"text":"From this observation alone,\nand clever mathematics,"},{"time":358774,"text":"Newton rightly deduced"},{"time":361104,"text":"that the Earth is a wee bit\nflattened at the poles,"},{"time":366669,"text":"like 0.3 percent --"},{"time":368843,"text":"so tiny that you wouldn't even\nnotice it on the real view of the Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374276,"text":"These stories show that mathematics"},{"time":378228,"text":"is able to make us go out of our intuition"},{"time":383512,"text":"measure the Earth which seems infinite,"},{"time":387021,"text":"see atoms which are invisible"},{"time":389339,"text":"or detect an imperceptible\nvariation of shape."},{"time":392744,"text":"And if there is just one thing that you\nshould take home from this talk,"},{"time":396615,"text":"it is this:"},{"time":397833,"text":"mathematics allows us\nto go beyond the intuition"},{"time":402235,"text":"and explore territories\nwhich do not fit within our grasp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407609,"text":"Here's a modern example\nyou will all relate to:"},{"time":411362,"text":"searching the Internet."},{"time":414037,"text":"The World Wide Web,"},{"time":415403,"text":"more than one billion web pages --"},{"time":417231,"text":"do you want to go through them all?"},{"time":419660,"text":"Computing power helps,"},{"time":421486,"text":"but it would be useless without\nthe mathematical modeling"},{"time":424696,"text":"to find the information\nhidden in the data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428491,"text":"Let's work out a baby problem."},{"time":431872,"text":"Imagine that you're a detective\nworking on a crime case,"},{"time":435703,"text":"and there are many people\nwho have their version of the facts."},{"time":440032,"text":"Who do you want to interview first?"},{"time":442681,"text":"Sensible answer:"},{"time":444620,"text":"prime witnesses."},{"time":446878,"text":"You see,"},{"time":448136,"text":"suppose that there is person number seven,"},{"time":452380,"text":"tells you a story,"},{"time":453555,"text":"but when you ask where he got if from,"},{"time":455593,"text":"he points to person\nnumber three as a source."},{"time":458653,"text":"And maybe person number three, in turn,"},{"time":460745,"text":"points at person number one\nas the primary source."},{"time":464465,"text":"Now number one is a prime witness,"},{"time":466150,"text":"so I definitely want\nto interview him -- priority."},{"time":470148,"text":"And from the graph"},{"time":471323,"text":"we also see that person\nnumber four is a prime witness."},{"time":474575,"text":"And maybe I even want\nto interview him first,"},{"time":477042,"text":"because there are more\npeople who refer to him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480354,"text":"OK, that was easy,"},{"time":483042,"text":"but now what about if you have\na big bunch of people who will testify?"},{"time":488864,"text":"And this graph,"},{"time":490240,"text":"I may think of it as all people\nwho testify in a complicated crime case,"},{"time":495883,"text":"but it may just as well be web pages\npointing to each other,"},{"time":499929,"text":"referring to each other for contents."},{"time":502878,"text":"Which ones are the most authoritative?"},{"time":505587,"text":"Not so clear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508091,"text":"Enter PageRank,"},{"time":510015,"text":"one of the early cornerstones of Google."},{"time":513337,"text":"This algorithm uses the laws\nof mathematical randomness"},{"time":517603,"text":"to determine automatically\nthe most relevant web pages,"},{"time":521484,"text":"in the same way as we used randomness\nin the Galton Board experiment."},{"time":527341,"text":"So let's send into this graph"},{"time":529706,"text":"a bunch of tiny, digital marbles"},{"time":532580,"text":"and let them go randomly\nthrough the graph."},{"time":536353,"text":"Each time they arrive at some site,"},{"time":538044,"text":"they will go out through some link\nchosen at random to the next one."},{"time":542234,"text":"And again, and again, and again."},{"time":544358,"text":"And with small, growing piles,"},{"time":546010,"text":"we'll keep the record of how many\ntimes each site has been visited"},{"time":549787,"text":"by these digital marbles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552243,"text":"Here we go."},{"time":553418,"text":"Randomness, randomness."},{"time":555811,"text":"And from time to time,"},{"time":557283,"text":"also let's make jumps completely\nrandomly to increase the fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562471,"text":"And look at this:"},{"time":564358,"text":"from the chaos will emerge the solution."},{"time":567483,"text":"The highest piles\ncorrespond to those sites"},{"time":569992,"text":"which somehow are better\nconnected than the others,"},{"time":573527,"text":"more pointed at than the others."},{"time":575824,"text":"And here we see clearly"},{"time":577570,"text":"which are the web pages\nwe want to first try."},{"time":581507,"text":"Once again,"},{"time":582682,"text":"the solution emerges from the randomness."},{"time":585775,"text":"Of course, since that time,"},{"time":588050,"text":"Google has come up with much more\nsophisticated algorithms,"},{"time":591781,"text":"but already this was beautiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594981,"text":"And still,"},{"time":596481,"text":"just one problem in a million."},{"time":598734,"text":"With the advent of digital area,"},{"time":601028,"text":"more and more problems lend\nthemselves to mathematical analysis,"},{"time":606068,"text":"making the job of mathematician\na more and more useful one,"},{"time":611166,"text":"to the extent that a few years ago,"},{"time":613912,"text":"it was ranked number one\namong hundreds of jobs"},{"time":617715,"text":"in a study about the best and worst jobs"},{"time":621707,"text":"published by the Wall Street\nJournal in 2009."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625445,"text":"Mathematician --"},{"time":627321,"text":"best job in the world."},{"time":629646,"text":"That's because of the applications:"},{"time":632738,"text":"communication theory,"},{"time":634901,"text":"information theory,"},{"time":636745,"text":"game theory,"},{"time":638029,"text":"compressed sensing,"},{"time":639499,"text":"machine learning,"},{"time":641085,"text":"graph analysis,"},{"time":642676,"text":"harmonic analysis."},{"time":644442,"text":"And why not stochastic processes,"},{"time":647106,"text":"linear programming,"},{"time":648760,"text":"or fluid simulation?"},{"time":651292,"text":"Each of these fields have\nmonster industrial applications."},{"time":655211,"text":"And through them,"},{"time":656386,"text":"there is big money in mathematics."},{"time":659400,"text":"And let me concede"},{"time":661464,"text":"that when it comes to making\nmoney from the math,"},{"time":663965,"text":"the Americans are by a long shot\nthe world champions,"},{"time":667813,"text":"with clever, emblematic billionaires\nand amazing, giant companies,"},{"time":672456,"text":"all resting, ultimately,\non good algorithm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677091,"text":"Now with all this beauty,\nusefulness and wealth,"},{"time":681087,"text":"mathematics does look more sexy."},{"time":684399,"text":"But don't you think"},{"time":686040,"text":"that the life a mathematical\nresearcher is an easy one."},{"time":690959,"text":"It is filled with perplexity,"},{"time":694347,"text":"frustration,"},{"time":696172,"text":"a desperate fight for understanding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699955,"text":"Let me evoke for you"},{"time":702119,"text":"one of the most striking days\nin my mathematician's life."},{"time":706523,"text":"Or should I say,"},{"time":707698,"text":"one of the most striking nights."},{"time":710713,"text":"At that time,"},{"time":711888,"text":"I was staying at the Institute\nfor Advanced Studies in Princeton --"},{"time":715063,"text":"for many years, the home\nof Albert Einstein"},{"time":717226,"text":"and arguably the most holy place\nfor mathematical research in the world."},{"time":722878,"text":"And that night I was working\nand working on an elusive proof,"},{"time":726746,"text":"which was incomplete."},{"time":729304,"text":"It was all about understanding"},{"time":731536,"text":"the paradoxical stability\nproperty of plasmas,"},{"time":735383,"text":"which are a crowd of electrons."},{"time":738423,"text":"In the perfect world of plasma,"},{"time":741183,"text":"there are no collisions"},{"time":742985,"text":"and no friction to provide\nthe stability like we are used to."},{"time":747392,"text":"But still,"},{"time":748567,"text":"if you slightly perturb\na plasma equilibrium,"},{"time":751624,"text":"you will find that the\nresulting electric field"},{"time":754336,"text":"spontaneously vanishes,"},{"time":756699,"text":"or damps out,"},{"time":758698,"text":"as if by some mysterious friction force."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762728,"text":"This paradoxical effect,"},{"time":764587,"text":"called the Landau damping,"},{"time":766088,"text":"is one of the most important\nin plasma physics,"},{"time":769101,"text":"and it was discovered\nthrough mathematical ideas."},{"time":772970,"text":"But still,"},{"time":774145,"text":"a full mathematical understanding\nof this phenomenon was missing."},{"time":778399,"text":"And together with my former student\nand main collaborator Cl√©ment Mouhot,"},{"time":783209,"text":"in Paris at the time,"},{"time":784725,"text":"we had been working for months\nand months on such a proof."},{"time":789832,"text":"Actually,"},{"time":791191,"text":"I had already announced by mistake\nthat we could solve it."},{"time":795961,"text":"But the truth is,"},{"time":797710,"text":"the proof was just not working."},{"time":800196,"text":"In spite of more than 100 pages\nof complicated, mathematical arguments,"},{"time":804569,"text":"and a bunch discoveries,"},{"time":806283,"text":"and huge calculation,"},{"time":807574,"text":"it was not working."},{"time":809290,"text":"And that night in Princeton,"},{"time":810995,"text":"a certain gap in the chain of arguments\nwas driving me crazy."},{"time":815658,"text":"I was putting in there all my energy\nand experience and tricks,"},{"time":820275,"text":"and still nothing was working."},{"time":822553,"text":"1 a.m., 2 a.m., 3 a.m.,"},{"time":826459,"text":"not working."},{"time":828545,"text":"Around 4 a.m., I go to bed in low spirits."},{"time":833915,"text":"Then a few hours later,"},{"time":836399,"text":"waking up and go,"},{"time":837574,"text":"\"Ah, it's time to get\nthe kids to school --\""},{"time":840955,"text":"What is this?"},{"time":842130,"text":"There was this voice in my head, I swear."},{"time":844894,"text":"\"Take the second term to the other side,"},{"time":846831,"text":"Fourier transform and invert in L2.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":849257,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":850432,"text":"Damn it,"},{"time":852158,"text":"that was the start of the solution!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":855519,"text":"You see,"},{"time":856694,"text":"I thought I had taken some rest,"},{"time":859001,"text":"but really my brain had\ncontinued to work on it."},{"time":863008,"text":"In those moments,"},{"time":864629,"text":"you don't think of your career\nor your colleagues,"},{"time":867254,"text":"it's just a complete battle\nbetween the problem and you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872098,"text":"That being said,"},{"time":873450,"text":"it does not harm when you do get\na promotion in reward for your hard work."},{"time":877808,"text":"And after we completed our huge\nanalysis of the Landau damping,"},{"time":882992,"text":"I was lucky enough"},{"time":884631,"text":"to get the most coveted Fields Medal"},{"time":887685,"text":"from the hands of the President of India,"},{"time":890576,"text":"in Hyderabad on 19 August, 2010 --"},{"time":895453,"text":"an honor that mathematicians\nnever dare to dream,"},{"time":898728,"text":"a day that I will remember until I live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902366,"text":"What do you think,"},{"time":903837,"text":"on such an occasion?"},{"time":906002,"text":"Pride, yes?"},{"time":907791,"text":"And gratitude to the many collaborators\nwho made this possible."},{"time":912304,"text":"And because it was a collective adventure,"},{"time":914540,"text":"you need to share it,\nnot just with your collaborators."},{"time":919548,"text":"I believe that everybody can appreciate\nthe thrill of mathematical research,"},{"time":925264,"text":"and share the passionate stories\nof humans and ideas behind it."},{"time":930494,"text":"And I've been working with my staff\nat Institut Henri Poincar√©,"},{"time":935292,"text":"together with partners and artists\nof mathematical communication worldwide,"},{"time":940497,"text":"so that we can found our own,\nvery special museum of mathematics there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946537,"text":"So in a few years,"},{"time":948885,"text":"when you come to Paris,"},{"time":950486,"text":"after tasting the great, crispy\nbaguette and macaroon,"},{"time":956168,"text":"please come and visit us\nat Institut Henri Poincar√©,"},{"time":959856,"text":"and share the mathematical dream with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":962395,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":963570,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}